eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The City of Johannesburg's newly appointed Public Safety MMC, David Tembe has assured that the CBD will be safer in six months. The city has deployed almost 2,000 Metro Police officers to beef up security in the crime-ridden CBD. READ: Gauteng police crack down on law breakers Criminals are being warned that their days of terrorising the community are numbered eNCA's Manqoba Mchunu reports in the video above.